# Normalize the auto-synced Azure skills to LF line endings.
#
# Why: the sync-azure-skills workflow rsyncs files straight from
# microsoft/azure-skills (which ship with CRLF) on a GitHub runner where git's
# core.autocrlf defaults to false. Without a normalization rule, every run would
# commit CRLF over the LF copy that local clients (e.g. core.autocrlf=input)
# produce — endless whitespace-only churn. Forcing LF here makes both the runner
# and local clients agree, so the workflow becomes a true no-op unless upstream
# content actually changes. text=auto still auto-detects and leaves binaries alone.
.github/skills/** text=auto eol=lf
